      <span class="es"><strong>Respuesta experta:</strong> Implementar el <strong>Ledger Approach</strong>. El Libro Mayor L&iacute;der (0L) refleja las normas IFRS del grupo. Para cada pa&iacute;s con GAAP local diferente, se activa un <strong>Libro Mayor No L&iacute;der</strong> por c&oacute;digo de empresa. Esto evita duplicar cuentas y permite informes paralelos sin impacto en CO.</span>
      <span class="en"><strong>Expert answer:</strong> Implement the <strong>Ledger Approach</strong>. The Leading Ledger (0L) reflects the group IFRS standards. For each country with a different local GAAP, activate a <strong>Non-Leading Ledger</strong> per company code. This avoids duplicating accounts and allows parallel reporting without impact on CO.</span>
