      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-amber">&#127991;</div><span class="es">Grupos de Cuentas, Field Status y Campos Clave al Crear Cuentas G/L</span><span class="en">Account Groups, Field Status and Key Fields When Creating G/L Accounts</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">C&oacute;mo crear un Account Group: t&eacute;cnica Copy as</span><span class="en">How to create an Account Group: Copy as technique</span></div>
        <p class="es" style="margin-top:6px">En Customizing, los Account Groups se crean <strong>copiando uno existente</strong> (bot&oacute;n <strong>Copy as...</strong> o F6), no con New Entries. Se selecciona el grupo de referencia, se copia y se modifican solo los campos necesarios (nombre y rango de n&uacute;meros). Esto hereda toda la configuraci&oacute;n de Field Status del grupo origen.</p>
        <p class="en" style="margin-top:6px">In Customizing, Account Groups are created by <strong>copying an existing one</strong> (<strong>Copy as...</strong> button or F6), not with New Entries. Select the reference group, copy it, then modify only the required fields (name and number range). This inherits all Field Status configuration from the source group.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">4 Estados del Field Status (Datos Maestros)</span><span class="en">4 Field Status States (Master Data)</span></div>
        <table>
          <tr><th><span class="es">Estado</span><span class="en">Status</span></th><th><span class="es">Significado</span><span class="en">Meaning</span></th><th><span class="es">Prioridad</span><span class="en">Priority</span></th></tr>
          <tr><td>Suppress</td><td><span class="es">Campo oculto. No puede combinarse con Required.</span><span class="en">Hidden field. Cannot be combined with Required.</span></td><td>1 (<span class="es">Mayor</span><span class="en">Highest</span>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Display</td><td><span class="es">Campo visible pero no modificable. Solo lectura.</span><span class="en">Visible field but not editable. Read-only.</span></td><td>2</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Required Entry</td><td><span class="es">El usuario DEBE ingresar un valor. Error si est&aacute; vac&iacute;o.</span><span class="en">User MUST enter a value. Error if left empty.</span></td><td>3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Optional Entry</td><td><span class="es">El usuario puede dejar el campo vac&iacute;o.</span><span class="en">User can leave the field empty.</span></td><td>4 (<span class="es">Menor</span><span class="en">Lowest</span>)</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="alert alert-amber" style="margin-top:10px">
          <strong><span class="es">Prioridad al combinar</span><span class="en">Priority when combining</span>: </strong>Suppress &gt; Display &gt; Required &gt; Optional.
          <span class="es"> Los campos &lsquo;Moneda de cuenta&rsquo; y &lsquo;Grupo de estado de campo&rsquo; son SIEMPRE obligatorios.</span>
          <span class="en"> The fields &lsquo;Account Currency&rsquo; and &lsquo;Field Status Group&rsquo; are ALWAYS required.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">Campos importantes al crear una cuenta G/L (Segmento del Plan de Cuentas)</span><span class="en">Important fields when creating a G/L account (Chart of Accounts Segment)</span></div>
        <div class="kv" style="margin-top:8px">
          <span class="kv-k">Group Account No.</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">N&uacute;mero de cuenta en el <strong>plan de cuentas de grupo</strong> para consolidaci&oacute;n corporativa. Se ingresa en el segmento del Plan de Cuentas (Consolidation Data). Es obligatorio cuando el grupo usa un plan de cuentas de grupo separado.</span><span class="en"><strong>Group chart of accounts</strong> account number used for corporate consolidation. Entered in the Chart of Accounts segment (Consolidation Data). Required when the group uses a separate group chart of accounts.</span></span>
          <span class="kv-k">P&amp;L Statement Acct Type</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Solo aplica a cuentas de <strong>P&amp;L (Ingresos/Gastos)</strong>. Define a qu&eacute; cuenta de Resultados Retenidos (Retained Earnings) se traspasa el saldo al cierre de ejercicio. Valor m&aacute;s com&uacute;n: <strong>X</strong>.</span><span class="en">Applies only to <strong>P&amp;L (Income/Expense)</strong> accounts. Defines which Retained Earnings account receives the balance at year-end. Most common value: <strong>X</strong>.</span></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">Cost Element Category &mdash; enlace G/L con Controlling (CO)</span><span class="en">Cost Element Category &mdash; G/L link to Controlling (CO)</span></div>
        <p class="es" style="margin-top:6px">Las cuentas G/L de tipo <strong>Primary Costs or Revenue</strong> funcionan simult&aacute;neamente como <strong>elementos de costo en CO</strong>. Al crear o mantener una cuenta de este tipo, en la secci&oacute;n <em>Controlling Data</em> del segmento del c&oacute;digo de empresa se debe asignar la <strong>Cost Element Category</strong>. Sin este dato, el sistema puede rechazar posteos que requieran asignaci&oacute;n de CO.</p>
        <p class="en" style="margin-top:6px">G/L accounts of type <strong>Primary Costs or Revenue</strong> simultaneously function as <strong>cost elements in CO</strong>. When creating or maintaining an account of this type, the <strong>Cost Element Category</strong> must be assigned in the <em>Controlling Data</em> section of the company code segment. Without this, the system may reject postings that require CO assignment.</p>
        <table style="margin-top:8px">
          <tr><th><span class="es">Categor&iacute;a</span><span class="en">Category</span></th><th><span class="es">Uso t&iacute;pico</span><span class="en">Typical use</span></th></tr>
          <tr><td>01</td><td><span class="es">Primary costs / cost-reducing revenues &mdash; la m&aacute;s habitual para cuentas de gasto e ingreso primario.</span><span class="en">Primary costs / cost-reducing revenues &mdash; most common for primary expense and revenue accounts.</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>11</td><td><span class="es">Revenues &mdash; para cuentas de ingreso en CO-PA.</span><span class="en">Revenues &mdash; for revenue accounts in CO-PA.</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>22</td><td><span class="es">External settlement &mdash; para liquidaciones externas.</span><span class="en">External settlement &mdash; for external settlements.</span></td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="alert alert-red" style="margin-top:10px">
          <strong>&#9888;&#65039; <span class="es">Error frecuente</span><span class="en">Common error</span>: </strong>
          <span class="es">Si una cuenta P&amp;L no tiene Cost Element Category asignada y el CO est&aacute; activo, el sistema dar&aacute; error al postear en esa cuenta con asignaci&oacute;n CO (Centro de Costo, Orden interna, etc.).</span>
          <span class="en">If a P&amp;L account has no Cost Element Category assigned and CO is active, the system will give an error when posting to that account with CO assignment (Cost Center, Internal Order, etc.).</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
