  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-green">&#127919;</div><span class="es">Centros de Beneficio, Segmentos e IFRS 8</span><span class="en">Profit Centers, Segments and IFRS 8</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="kv">
        <span class="kv-k">Segment</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Divisi&oacute;n para estados financieros externos. Requerido por IFRS 8 y ASC 280.</span><span class="en">Division for external financial statements. Required by IFRS 8 and ASC 280.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Profit Center</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Reporting interno. El segmento se deriva del Profit Center autom&aacute;ticamente.</span><span class="en">Internal reporting. The segment is automatically derived from the Profit Center.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k"><span class="es">Derivaci&oacute;n</span><span class="en">Derivation</span></span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Si el PC no tiene segmento asignado, no hay derivaci&oacute;n autom&aacute;tica.</span><span class="en">If the PC has no segment assigned, there is no automatic derivation.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k"><span class="es">M&aacute;x. PC</span><span class="en">Max. PC</span></span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">5.000 centros de beneficio por cliente (recomendaci&oacute;n SAP).</span><span class="en">5,000 profit centers per client (SAP recommendation).</span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-green" style="margin-top:10px">
        <strong><span class="es">Cadena de derivaci&oacute;n</span><span class="en">Derivation chain</span>: </strong>
        <span class="es">Cost Center &rarr; Profit Center &rarr; Segment. Al asignar el CC en el posting, SAP deriva autom&aacute;ticamente el PC y el Segment.</span>
        <span class="en">Cost Center &rarr; Profit Center &rarr; Segment. When assigning the CC in posting, SAP automatically derives the PC and Segment.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-purple">&#128101;</div>Business Partner &amp; CVI</div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="es">El Business Partner (BP) es el <strong>punto &uacute;nico de entrada</strong> para gestionar clientes y proveedores en SAP S/4HANA.</p>
      <p class="en">The Business Partner (BP) is the <strong>single entry point</strong> for managing customers and vendors in SAP S/4HANA.</p>
      <div class="kv" style="margin-top:10px">
        <span class="kv-k">FLCU00</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Rol FI Customer &mdash; rol est&aacute;ndar de SAP para clientes. Es el rol que activa el segmento financiero del cliente en el BP.</span><span class="en">FI Customer role &mdash; SAP standard role for customers. This is the role that activates the financial customer segment in the BP.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">FLVN00</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Rol FI Vendor &mdash; rol est&aacute;ndar de SAP para proveedores.</span><span class="en">FI Vendor role &mdash; SAP standard role for vendors.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">CVI</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Vincula el BP con cuentas FI. Asignaci&oacute;n 1:1. Un BP = un cliente/proveedor.</span><span class="en">Links the BP with FI accounts. 1:1 assignment. One BP = one customer/vendor.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Same Numbers</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Para que BP y customer usen el mismo n&uacute;mero: marcar &ldquo;Same Numbers&rdquo; y declarar el number range del Customer Account Group como <strong>externo</strong>.</span><span class="en">For BP and customer to share the same number: check &ldquo;Same Numbers&rdquo; and declare the Customer Account Group number range as <strong>external</strong>.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k"><span class="es">Campos Sensibles</span><span class="en">Sensitive Fields</span></span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Campos cr&iacute;ticos (datos bancarios, cuenta reconciliaci&oacute;n) que requieren confirmaci&oacute;n por otro usuario. Doble control. Tx FK08.</span><span class="en">Critical fields (bank data, reconciliation account) requiring confirmation by another user. Dual control. Tx FK08.</span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">Las 3 fuentes de Field Status para clientes/proveedores</span><span class="en">The 3 Field Status sources for customers/vendors</span></div>
        <p class="es" style="margin-top:6px">Cuando se trabaja con datos maestros de clientes o proveedores, el campo que el usuario ve en pantalla es el resultado de <strong>combinar tres fuentes de field status</strong> simultan&eacute;amente (se aplica la prioridad m&aacute;s restrictiva):</p>
        <p class="en" style="margin-top:6px">When working with customer or vendor master data, the field the user sees on screen is the result of <strong>combining three field status sources</strong> simultaneously (the most restrictive priority applies):</p>
        <table style="margin-top:8px">
          <tr><th>#</th><th><span class="es">Fuente</span><span class="en">Source</span></th><th>IMG Path</th></tr>
          <tr><td>1</td><td><strong><span class="es">Account Group</span><span class="en">Account Group</span></strong><br><span class="es" style="font-size:11px">Controla campos seg&uacute;n el grupo de cuentas del BP (ej. D##).</span><span class="en" style="font-size:11px">Controls fields based on the BP account group (e.g. D##).</span></td><td style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:10px">FA &rarr; AR/AP &rarr; Customer Accounts &rarr; Master Data &rarr; Define Account Groups with Screen Layout</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td><strong><span class="es">Activity (Screen Layout per Activity)</span><span class="en">Activity (Screen Layout per Activity)</span></strong><br><span class="es" style="font-size:11px">Controla campos seg&uacute;n la actividad: Create, Change, Display. Aplica a <strong>todos</strong> los clientes en esa actividad.</span><span class="en" style="font-size:11px">Controls fields based on the activity: Create, Change, Display. Applies to <strong>all</strong> customers in that activity.</span></td><td style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:10px">FA &rarr; AR/AP &rarr; Customer Accounts &rarr; Master Data &rarr; Define Screen Layout per Activity (Customers)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td><strong><span class="es">BP Role (Configure Field Attributes per BP Role)</span><span class="en">BP Role (Configure Field Attributes per BP Role)</span></strong><br><span class="es" style="font-size:11px">Controla campos espec&iacute;ficos al rol del BP. Aplica &uacute;nicamente al rol seleccionado. No recomendado para uso general.</span><span class="en" style="font-size:11px">Controls fields specific to the BP role. Applies only to the selected role. Not recommended for general use.</span></td><td style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:10px">Cross-App &rarr; SAP BP &rarr; Basic Settings &rarr; Field Groupings &rarr; Configure Field Attributes per BP Role</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="alert alert-blue" style="margin-top:10px">
          <strong><span class="es">Ejemplo pr&aacute;ctico</span><span class="en">Practical example</span>: </strong>
          <span class="es">Si el campo <em>Sort Key</em> es &ldquo;Optional&rdquo; en el Account Group D## pero &ldquo;Display&rdquo; en la Activity <em>Change Customer</em> &rarr; el campo se muestra en modo <strong>solo lectura</strong> al modificar el cliente (Display gana sobre Optional). Esta regla es independiente del Account Group.</span>
          <span class="en">If the <em>Sort Key</em> field is &ldquo;Optional&rdquo; in Account Group D## but &ldquo;Display&rdquo; in the Activity <em>Change Customer</em> &rarr; the field is shown as <strong>read-only</strong> when changing the customer (Display wins over Optional). This rule is independent of the Account Group.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">Ceros iniciales en rangos de n&uacute;meros de cliente/proveedor</span><span class="en">Leading zeros in customer/vendor number ranges</span></div>
        <div class="alert alert-red" style="margin-top:6px">
          <strong>&#9888;&#65039; <span class="es">Regla cr&iacute;tica</span><span class="en">Critical rule</span>: </strong>
          <span class="es">Al definir rangos de n&uacute;meros para cuentas de cliente (Customer Account Number Ranges), los n&uacute;meros deben introducirse <strong>con todos sus ceros al inicio</strong>, hasta completar la longitud m&aacute;xima del campo. Si el rango es 200100 a 200199, en el sistema debe ingresarse como <strong>000200100 a 000200199</strong>. Omitir los ceros iniciales provoca un error de sistema o un solapamiento con otros rangos.</span>
          <span class="en">When defining number ranges for Customer Accounts (Customer Account Number Ranges), numbers must be entered <strong>with all leading zeros</strong> to fill the maximum field length. If the range is 200100 to 200199, it must be entered in the system as <strong>000200100 to 000200199</strong>. Omitting leading zeros causes a system error or overlap with other ranges.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="scenario">
    <div class="s-label">&#128293; <span class="es">Escenario de Examen 2026</span><span class="en">2026 Exam Scenario</span></div>
    <div class="s-q">
      <span class="es">&#10067; El auditor reporta asientos directos en la cuenta 20000 (Cuentas por Pagar). &iquest;Qu&eacute; configuraci&oacute;n impide esto?</span>
      <span class="en">&#10067; The auditor reports direct postings to account 20000 (Accounts Payable). What configuration prevents this?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="s-a">
      <span class="es"><strong>Respuesta experta:</strong> La cuenta 20000 debe ser una <strong>cuenta de RECONCILIACI&Oacute;N para proveedores</strong>. En el segmento del CoCd de la cuenta G/L, el campo &lsquo;Reconciliation Account for Account Type&rsquo; debe tener el valor <strong>'K'</strong>. Esto bloquea autom&aacute;ticamente los asientos directos.</span>
      <span class="en"><strong>Expert answer:</strong> Account 20000 must be a <strong>RECONCILIATION account for vendors</strong>. In the company code segment of the G/L account, the field &lsquo;Reconciliation Account for Account Type&rsquo; must have the value <strong>'K'</strong>. This automatically blocks direct postings.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sec-title"><span class="es">Resumen del M&oacute;dulo</span><span class="en">Module Summary</span></div>
  <div class="alert alert-red">
    <span class="es"><strong>&#10003; Cuenta G/L &mdash; 2 segmentos:</strong> Plan de Cuentas (global, todos los CoCd) + C&oacute;digo de Empresa (local, espec&iacute;fico).<br><strong>&#10003; Account Groups:</strong> crear con Copy as... Incluir Group Account Number, P&amp;L Statement Acct Type y Cost Element Category (01) para cuentas P&amp;L.<br><strong>&#10003; Reconciliaci&oacute;n:</strong> NUNCA asientos directos. Solo v&iacute;a subledger. OIM: solo activa/desactiva con saldo CERO.<br><strong>&#10003; Segmentos + IFRS 8:</strong> siempre con Profit Centers. Derivaci&oacute;n autom&aacute;tica. M&aacute;x. 5.000 PC recomendados.<br><strong>&#10003; BP + CVI:</strong> punto &uacute;nico de entrada. FLCU00/FLVN00 est&aacute;ndar. Same Numbers requiere NR externo. Ceros iniciales obligatorios. 3 fuentes de Field Status.</span><span class="en"><strong>&#10003; G/L Account &mdash; 2 segments:</strong> Chart of Accounts (global, all CoCd) + Company Code (local, specific).<br><strong>&#10003; Account Groups:</strong> create with Copy as... Include Group Account Number, P&amp;L Statement Acct Type and Cost Element Category (01) for P&amp;L accounts.<br><strong>&#10003; Reconciliation:</strong> NEVER direct postings. Only via subledger. OIM: activate/deactivate only with ZERO balance.<br><strong>&#10003; Segments + IFRS 8:</strong> always with Profit Centers. Automatic derivation. Max. 5,000 PC recommended.<br><strong>&#10003; BP + CVI:</strong> single entry point. FLCU00/FLVN00 standard. Same Numbers requires external NR. Leading zeros mandatory. 3 Field Status sources.</span>
  </div>
</div>
