<div class="view" id="m5">
  <div class="page-brand"><span>&#9670; Valentina RF</span> &middot; S4F12 Certification Guide 2026</div>
  <div class="mod-header">
    <span class="mod-num">M5</span>
    <div>
      <h2><span class="es">Control de Documentos FI</span><span class="en">FI Document Control</span></h2>
      <p><span class="es">Principio de Documento &middot; Tipos &middot; Rangos &middot; Posting Keys &middot; Field Status &middot; Per&iacute;odos &middot; Tolerancias</span><span class="en">Document Principle &middot; Types &middot; Ranges &middot; Posting Keys &middot; Field Status &middot; Periods &middot; Tolerances</span></p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="exam-tip">
    <div class="label">&#128204; <span class="es">Claves del Examen</span><span class="en">Exam Keys</span></div>
    <p class="es">Identificador &uacute;nico = N&uacute;mero + CoCd + A&ntilde;o fiscal. Tipo &lsquo;+&rsquo; es el portero de todos los per&iacute;odos. Field Status en documentos: 3 prioridades (no 4). Park &ne; Post &ne; Hold.</p>
    <p class="en">Unique identifier = Number + CoCd + Fiscal Year. Type &lsquo;+&rsquo; is the gatekeeper of all periods. Field Status in documents: 3 priorities (not 4). Park &ne; Post &ne; Hold.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card open">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-blue">&#128196;</div><span class="es">El Principio de Documento</span><span class="en">The Document Principle</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="alert alert-blue">
        <strong><span class="es">Identificador &uacute;nico</span><span class="en">Unique identifier</span>: </strong>
        <span class="es">N&uacute;mero de documento + C&oacute;digo de empresa + A&ntilde;o fiscal.</span>
        <span class="en">Document number + Company code + Fiscal year.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="two-col" style="margin-top:10px">
        <div class="mini-card">
          <div class="mt"><span class="es">Encabezado del Documento</span><span class="en">Document Header</span></div>
          <p class="es">Tipo de documento, fecha de publicaci&oacute;n, fecha del documento, moneda, texto. Aplica a todo el documento.</p>
          <p class="en">Document type, posting date, document date, currency, text. Applies to the entire document.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-card">
          <div class="mt"><span class="es">Partidas Individuales</span><span class="en">Line Items</span></div>
          <p class="es">M&iacute;nimo 2 l&iacute;neas (d&eacute;bito + cr&eacute;dito). El documento debe equilibrarse a CERO.</p>
          <p class="en">Minimum 2 lines (debit + credit). The document must balance to ZERO.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-green">&#128290;</div><span class="es">Tipos de Documento y Rangos de N&uacute;mero</span><span class="en">Document Types and Number Ranges</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="es"><span class="es">Se definen a nivel de <strong>cliente</strong> (v&aacute;lidos para todos los CoCd). Controlan: rango de n&uacute;meros, tipo de reversa, tipos de cuenta permitidos y datos de control.</span></p>
      <p class="en"><span class="en">Defined at <strong>client</strong> level (valid for all CoCd). Control: number range, reversal type, allowed account types and control data.</span></p>
      <table style="margin-top:10px">
        <tr><th>Doc. Type</th><th><span class="es">Uso est&aacute;ndar</span><span class="en">Standard use</span></th></tr>
        <tr><td>SA</td><td><span class="es">Publicaciones en todos los tipos de cuenta (uso general / G/L manual)</span><span class="en">Postings to all account types (general use / manual G/L)</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>KR</td><td><span class="es">Factura de proveedor manual</span><span class="en">Manual vendor invoice</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>DR</td><td><span class="es">Factura de cliente manual</span><span class="en">Manual customer invoice</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>DZ</td><td><span class="es">Pago de cliente</span><span class="en">Customer payment</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>AB</td><td><span class="es">Documento gen&eacute;rico &mdash; tambi&eacute;n usado como Reverse Doc Type</span><span class="en">Generic document &mdash; also used as Reverse Doc Type</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>RV / RE</td><td><span class="es">Facturas generadas por SD / MM</span><span class="en">Invoices generated by SD / MM</span></td></tr>
      </table>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">Tipos de Numeraci&oacute;n</span><span class="en">Numbering Types</span></div>
        <table>
          <tr><th><span class="es">Tipo</span><span class="en">Type</span></th><th><span class="es">Descripci&oacute;n</span><span class="en">Description</span></th></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="es">Interna</span><span class="en">Internal</span></td><td><span class="es">SAP asigna autom&aacute;ticamente. El usuario no interviene.</span><span class="en">SAP assigns automatically. User does not intervene.</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="es">Externa</span><span class="en">External</span></td><td><span class="es">El usuario ingresa el n&uacute;mero manualmente (ej. n&uacute;mero de factura del proveedor).</span><span class="en">User enters the number manually (e.g. vendor invoice number).</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="es">Continuo</span><span class="en">Continuous</span></td><td><span class="es">Contin&uacute;a desde el &uacute;ltimo n&uacute;mero usado en el nuevo a&ntilde;o fiscal.</span><span class="en">Continues from the last number used in the new fiscal year.</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="es">Por a&ntilde;o fiscal</span><span class="en">Per fiscal year</span></td><td><span class="es">Reinicia desde el primer n&uacute;mero del rango al inicio de cada a&ntilde;o.</span><span class="en">Restarts from the first number of the range at the start of each year.</span></td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="alert alert-green" style="margin-top:10px">
          <strong>RFBNUM00: </strong><span class="es">Reporte para detectar <strong>brechas en la numeraci&oacute;n</strong> de documentos (gaps en la secuencia). Los n&uacute;meros son espec&iacute;ficos por a&ntilde;o fiscal y un rango puede asignarse a varios tipos de documento.</span><span class="en">Report to detect <strong>numbering gaps</strong> in document sequences. Numbers are specific per fiscal year and a range can be assigned to multiple document types.</span><br>
          <strong>RFBABL00: </strong><span class="es">Reporte de <strong>auditor&iacute;a de cambios</strong> en documentos publicados. Muestra: campo modificado, valor anterior, valor nuevo, usuario, fecha y hora del cambio.</span><span class="en"><strong>Document change audit</strong> report. Shows: modified field, old value, new value, user, date and time of the change.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-amber">&#128273;</div><span class="es">Claves de Publicaci&oacute;n (Posting Keys)</span><span class="en">Posting Keys</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="es">Se definen a nivel de <strong>cliente</strong>. Controlan cada partida individual: tipo de cuenta, indicador d&eacute;bito/cr&eacute;dito y field status de los campos de la partida.</p>
      <p class="en">Defined at <strong>client</strong> level. Control each line item: account type, debit/credit indicator and field status of the line item fields.</p>
      <div class="kv" style="margin-top:10px">
        <span class="kv-k">G/L (S)</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es"><strong>40</strong> = d&eacute;bito &middot; <strong>50</strong> = cr&eacute;dito. Solo se necesitan estas dos para cuentas G/L.</span><span class="en"><strong>40</strong> = debit &middot; <strong>50</strong> = credit. Only these two are needed for G/L accounts.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Customer (D)</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">01 = factura (d&eacute;b.) &middot; 11 = nota de cr&eacute;dito &middot; 15 = pago entrante</span><span class="en">01 = invoice (debit) &middot; 11 = credit memo &middot; 15 = incoming payment</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Vendor (K)</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">31 = factura (cr&eacute;d.) &middot; 21 = nota de cr&eacute;dito &middot; 25 = pago saliente</span><span class="en">31 = invoice (credit) &middot; 21 = credit memo &middot; 25 = outgoing payment</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k"><span class="es">Tipos de cuenta</span><span class="en">Account types</span></span><span class="kv-v">S = G/L &middot; D = Customer &middot; K = Vendor &middot; A = Asset &middot; M = Material</span>
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-amber" style="margin-top:10px">
        <strong>&#9888;&#65039; <span class="es">Clave examen</span><span class="en">Exam key</span>: </strong>
        <span class="es">SAP recomienda <strong>no modificar</strong> las posting keys est&aacute;ndar entregadas. Si se crean nuevas, hay que actualizar todas las tablas que las referencian. Las posting keys est&aacute;n definidas a nivel de cliente, no por c&oacute;digo de empresa.</span>
        <span class="en">SAP recommends <strong>not modifying</strong> the standard delivered posting keys. If new ones are created, all tables that reference them must be updated. Posting keys are defined at client level, not per company code.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-red">&#128203;</div><span class="es">Field Status Groups en Documentos &mdash; 3 Prioridades</span><span class="en">Field Status Groups in Documents &mdash; 3 Priorities</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="alert alert-red">
        <strong>SUPPRESS/HIDE</strong> (<span class="es">mayor</span><span class="en">highest</span>) &gt; <strong>REQUIRED ENTRY</strong> &gt; <strong>OPTIONAL ENTRY</strong> (<span class="es">menor</span><span class="en">lowest</span>)<br>
        <span class="es">SUPPRESS + REQUIRED en el mismo campo = <strong>error al publicar.</strong></span>
        <span class="en">SUPPRESS + REQUIRED on the same field = <strong>posting error.</strong></span>
      </div>
      <div class="kv" style="margin-top:10px">
        <span class="kv-k">Field Status Variant</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Contenedor de FSG. Se asigna al c&oacute;digo de empresa. Ejemplo: 0010</span><span class="en">FSG container. Assigned to the company code. Example: 0010</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Field Status Group</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Agrupa campos por comportamiento. Se asigna en el segmento CoCd de la cuenta GL. Ej: G001</span><span class="en">Groups fields by behavior. Assigned in the CoCd segment of the GL account. Ex: G001</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">IMG Path</span><span class="kv-v">FA Global Settings &rarr; Ledgers &rarr; Fields &rarr; Define Field Status Variants</span>
        <span class="kv-k"><span class="es">Nota</span><span class="en">Note</span></span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Si se publica en cuenta de subledger, SAP usa el FSG de la CUENTA DE RECONCILIACI&Oacute;N.</span><span class="en">If posting to a subledger account, SAP uses the FSG of the RECONCILIATION ACCOUNT.</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-blue">&#128198;</div><span class="es">Per&iacute;odos de Publicaci&oacute;n</span><span class="en">Posting Periods</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="alert alert-blue">
        <span class="es"><strong>El tipo de cuenta &lsquo;+&rsquo;</strong> es el &ldquo;portero&rdquo; de todos los per&iacute;odos. Si &lsquo;+&rsquo; est&aacute; cerrado para un per&iacute;odo, ning&uacute;n otro tipo de cuenta puede publicar en &eacute;l.</span>
        <span class="en"><strong>Account type &lsquo;+&rsquo;</strong> is the &ldquo;gatekeeper&rdquo; of all periods. If &lsquo;+&rsquo; is closed for a period, no other account type can post to it.</span>
