  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-red">&#8617;&#65039;</div><span class="es">Reversa: Normal vs. Publicaci&oacute;n Negativa</span><span class="en">Reversal: Normal vs. Negative Posting</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="mini-card">
          <div class="mt"><span class="es">Reversa Normal</span><span class="en">Normal Reversal</span></div>
          <p class="es">El d&eacute;bito incorrecto se publica como cr&eacute;dito. Las cifras de transacci&oacute;n <strong>AUMENTAN</strong>. M&eacute;todo est&aacute;ndar.</p>
          <p class="en">The incorrect debit is posted as a credit. Transaction figures <strong>INCREASE</strong>. Standard method.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-card">
          <div class="mt"><span class="es">Publicaci&oacute;n Negativa &#11088;</span><span class="en">Negative Posting &#11088;</span></div>
          <p class="es">Las cifras de transacci&oacute;n <strong>VUELVEN al estado previo</strong>. Requiere: (1) CoCd habilitado Y (2) raz&oacute;n de reversa configurada.</p>
          <p class="en">Transaction figures <strong>RETURN to the prior state</strong>. Requires: (1) CoCd enabled AND (2) reversal reason configured.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-red" style="margin-top:10px">
        <span class="es"><strong>&#9888;&#65039; Restricci&oacute;n:</strong> No se pueden reversar documentos con partidas COMPENSADAS. Primero: Reset Cleared Items, luego reversar.</span>
        <span class="en"><strong>&#9888;&#65039; Restriction:</strong> Cannot reverse documents with CLEARED items. First: Reset Cleared Items, then reverse.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-green">&#128178;</div><span class="es">Condiciones de Pago, Descuentos y Parameter IDs</span><span class="en">Payment Terms, Discounts and Parameter IDs</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="kv">
        <span class="kv-k">Baseline Date</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Punto de partida para calcular la fecha de vencimiento. Puede ser: Posting Date, Document Date, Entry Date, o fecha fija.</span><span class="en">Starting point for calculating the due date. Options: Posting Date, Document Date, Entry Date, or fixed date.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Day Limits</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Permiten definir condiciones diferentes seg&uacute;n el d&iacute;a del mes en que llega la factura. Todo dentro de una misma clave de condici&oacute;n de pago.</span><span class="en">Allow defining different conditions based on the day of the month the invoice arrives. All within the same payment condition key.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">Block Key</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Bloquea la partida para el proceso de pago autom&aacute;tico. <strong>Principio de doble control</strong>: un usuario crea la factura y otro la libera para pago eliminando el bloqueo.</span><span class="en">Blocks the line item for the automatic payment process. <strong>Dual control principle</strong>: one user creates the invoice and another releases it for payment by removing the block.</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k">IMG Path</span><span class="kv-v">FA &rarr; AR/AP &rarr; Business Transactions &rarr; Incoming Invoices &rarr; Maintain Terms of Payment</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title"><span class="es">Origen de condiciones de pago por m&oacute;dulo</span><span class="en">Payment terms source by module</span></div>
        <table>
          <tr><th><span class="es">M&oacute;dulo</span><span class="en">Module</span></th><th><span class="es">Fuente</span><span class="en">Source</span></th></tr>
          <tr><td>FI (<span class="es">manual</span><span class="en">manual</span>)</td><td><span class="es">Segmento del c&oacute;digo de empresa del Business Partner.</span><span class="en">Company code segment of the Business Partner.</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>SD (<span class="es">factura de venta</span><span class="en">sales invoice</span>)</td><td><span class="es">Segmento del &aacute;rea de ventas del BP. Se copian autom&aacute;ticamente al crear la factura FI.</span><span class="en">BP sales area segment. Copied automatically when creating the FI invoice.</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>MM (<span class="es">factura de proveedor</span><span class="en">vendor invoice</span>)</td><td><span class="es">Segmento de la organizaci&oacute;n de compras del BP. Se copian autom&aacute;ticamente al documento contable.</span><span class="en">BP purchasing org. segment. Copied automatically to the accounting document.</span></td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="sub">
        <div class="sub-title">Parameter IDs &mdash; <span class="es">Valores predeterminados de usuario</span><span class="en">User default values</span></div>
        <p class="es" style="margin-top:6px">Los <strong>Parameter IDs</strong> permiten al usuario definir valores predeterminados para campos que no cambian frecuentemente (c&oacute;digo de empresa, moneda, etc.). Se configuran en el perfil del usuario (SU3 o en Fiori &rarr; Settings &rarr; Default Values). Evitan errores de entrada y agilizan el trabajo diario. El sistema tambi&eacute;n propone autom&aacute;ticamente: la fecha actual como fecha de publicaci&oacute;n, y el mismo c&oacute;digo de empresa del &uacute;ltimo documento publicado.</p>
        <p class="en" style="margin-top:6px"><strong>Parameter IDs</strong> allow users to set default values for fields that do not change frequently (company code, currency, etc.). Configured in the user profile (SU3 or Fiori &rarr; Settings &rarr; Default Values). They prevent entry errors and speed up daily work. The system also automatically proposes: today's date as the posting date, and the same company code as the last posted document.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-blue">&#9998;</div><span class="es">Control de Cambios en Documentos Publicados</span><span class="en">Change Control in Posted Documents</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="es">Solo ciertos campos pueden modificarse en documentos ya publicados. Los campos que afectan a la conciliaci&oacute;n contable <strong>nunca</strong> pueden cambiarse.</p>
      <p class="en">Only certain fields can be modified in already posted documents. Fields affecting accounting reconciliation can <strong>never</strong> be changed.</p>
      <div class="two-col" style="margin-top:10px">
        <div class="mini-card">
          <div class="mt"><span class="es">&#10003; S&iacute; modificables</span><span class="en">&#10003; Modifiable</span></div>
          <p class="es">N&uacute;mero de referencia &middot; Texto del encabezado &middot; Campo de asignaci&oacute;n (BSEG-ZUONR) &middot; Campo de texto de la partida &middot; Condiciones de pago</p>
          <p class="en">Reference number &middot; Header text &middot; Assignment field (BSEG-ZUONR) &middot; Line item text &middot; Payment terms</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-card">
          <div class="mt"><span class="es">&#10007; NO modificables</span><span class="en">&#10007; NOT modifiable</span></div>
          <p class="es">Importe &middot; Posting key &middot; Cuenta &middot; Moneda &mdash; cualquier campo que afecte la conciliaci&oacute;n</p>
          <p class="en">Amount &middot; Posting key &middot; Account &middot; Currency &mdash; any field affecting reconciliation</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="kv" style="margin-top:10px">
        <span class="kv-k">IMG Path</span><span class="kv-v">FA Global Settings &rarr; Document &rarr; Rules for Changing Documents &rarr; Document Change Rules, Line Item</span>
        <span class="kv-k">RFBABL00</span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Reporte de auditor&iacute;a: muestra todos los cambios realizados en documentos (campo, valor anterior y nuevo, usuario, fecha/hora).</span><span class="en">Audit report: shows all changes made to documents (field, old and new value, user, date/time).</span></span>
        <span class="kv-k"><span class="es">Condici&oacute;n</span><span class="en">Condition</span></span><span class="kv-v"><span class="es">Un campo solo es modificable si: el per&iacute;odo sigue abierto, la partida NO est&aacute; compensada, y el campo est&aacute; configurado como modificable en las reglas de cambio.</span><span class="en">A field is only modifiable if: the period is still open, the line item is NOT cleared, and the field is configured as modifiable in the change rules.</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
      <div class="card-title"><div class="ci ci-amber">&#129534;</div><span class="es">Tax Category en Cuentas G/L</span><span class="en">Tax Category in G/L Accounts</span></div>
      <span class="chevron">&#8250;</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <table>
        <tr><th><span class="es">Valor</span><span class="en">Value</span></th><th><span class="es">Significado</span><span class="en">Meaning</span></th></tr>
        <tr><td>&ldquo; &rdquo; (<span class="es">blanco</span><span class="en">blank</span>)</td><td><span class="es">NO relevante para impuestos. Ej: cuentas bancarias.</span><span class="en">NOT tax-relevant. Ex: bank accounts.</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>-</td><td><span class="es">Requiere c&oacute;digo de impuesto de ENTRADA (input tax). T&iacute;pico en reconciliaci&oacute;n AP.</span><span class="en">Requires INPUT tax code. Typical in AP reconciliation accounts.</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>+</td><td><span class="es">Requiere c&oacute;digo de impuesto de SALIDA (output tax). T&iacute;pico en reconciliaci&oacute;n AR.</span><span class="en">Requires OUTPUT tax code. Typical in AR reconciliation accounts.</span></td></tr>
