  <!-- U3 -->

  <div class="sec-title" data-unit="u3">U3 &mdash; Master Data</div>
  <div class="ex-card" data-unit="u3"><div class="ex-header" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="ex-num">EJ 7</span><div><div class="ex-title"><span class="es">Create Account Groups for G/L Accounts &amp; Create G/L Accounts</span><span class="en">Create Account Groups for G/L Accounts &amp; Create G/L Accounts</span></div><div class="ex-sub">YCOA &middot; Copy as &middot; Cost Element &middot; Group Account No. &middot; P&amp;L Acct Type</div></div><span class="chevron">&#8250;</span></div>
    <div class="ex-body">
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Crear Account Groups &mdash; t&eacute;cnica Copy as</span><span class="en">Create Account Groups &mdash; Copy as technique</span>:</strong><span class="step-path">FA &rarr; GL &rarr; Master Data &rarr; G/L Accounts &rarr; Preparations &rarr; Define Account Group</span>
        <span class="es">Seleccionar el grupo de referencia (ej. ERG.) &rarr; bot&oacute;n <strong>Copy as...</strong> (F6) &rarr; cambiar solo el nombre del grupo y el rango de n&uacute;meros. NO usar New Entries &mdash; el Copy as hereda toda la configuraci&oacute;n de Field Status.</span>
        <span class="en">Select the reference group (e.g. ERG.) &rarr; <strong>Copy as...</strong> button (F6) &rarr; change only the group name and number range. Do NOT use New Entries &mdash; Copy as inherits all Field Status configuration.</span>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Crear cuenta G/L (Segmento del Plan de Cuentas)</span><span class="en">Create G/L Account (Chart of Accounts Segment)</span>:</strong>
        <span class="es">Fiori <strong>Manage G/L Account Master Data</strong> &rarr; Create &rarr; completar campos:</span>
        <span class="en">Fiori <strong>Manage G/L Account Master Data</strong> &rarr; Create &rarr; fill in fields:</span>
        <span class="step-path">G/L Account Type: Primary Costs or Revenue (para cuentas de gasto/ingreso) | Account Group: AE## | Short Text + Long Text | Group Account Number: (n&uacute;mero del plan de cuentas de grupo, ej. 0051100000) | P&amp;L Statement Acct Type: X</span>
        <div class="alert alert-blue" style="margin-top:8px">
          <strong>Group Account Number: </strong><span class="es">es el n&uacute;mero de cuenta en el plan de cuentas del grupo corporativo. Se rellena en la secci&oacute;n <em>Consolidation Data</em>. Es obligatorio si el grupo usa un plan de cuentas de grupo para consolidaci&oacute;n.</span><span class="en">is the account number in the corporate group chart of accounts. It is filled in the <em>Consolidation Data</em> section. Required if the group uses a group chart of accounts for consolidation.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="alert alert-amber" style="margin-top:6px">
          <strong>P&amp;L Statement Acct Type: </strong><span class="es">solo para cuentas de P&amp;L. Define a qu&eacute; cuenta de Retained Earnings se traspasa el saldo al cierre. El valor m&aacute;s habitual es <strong>X</strong>. Las cuentas Balance Sheet no tienen este campo.</span><span class="en">only for P&amp;L accounts. Defines which Retained Earnings account receives the balance at year-end. The most common value is <strong>X</strong>. Balance Sheet accounts do not have this field.</span>
        </div>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Crear Segmento del C&oacute;digo de Empresa</span><span class="en">Create Company Code Segment</span>:</strong>
        <span class="step-path">Account Currency: EUR | Tax Category: (seg&uacute;n tipo: &ldquo;-&rdquo; para gastos con IVA soportado) | Sort Key | Field Status Group (ej. YB03)</span>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Controlling Data &mdash; Cost Element Category (OBLIGATORIO para cuentas P&amp;L)</span><span class="en">Controlling Data &mdash; Cost Element Category (MANDATORY for P&amp;L accounts)</span>:</strong>
        <span class="es">En la misma pantalla de la cuenta, secci&oacute;n <em>Controlling Data</em>: asignar <strong>Cost Element Category = 01</strong> (Primary costs/cost-reducing revenues). Sin este dato, el sistema rechazar&aacute; posteos que requieran asignaci&oacute;n de CO (Centro de Costo, Orden, etc.).</span>
        <span class="en">On the same account screen, <em>Controlling Data</em> section: assign <strong>Cost Element Category = 01</strong> (Primary costs/cost-reducing revenues). Without this, the system will reject postings that require CO assignment (Cost Center, Order, etc.).</span>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Copiar una cuenta existente para crear la segunda r&aacute;pidamente</span><span class="en">Copy an existing account to create the second one quickly</span>:</strong>
        <span class="es">En Fiori Manage G/L Account Master Data, con la cuenta AE0001## en pantalla &rarr; bot&oacute;n <strong>Copy</strong> &rarr; ingresar el nuevo n&uacute;mero y cambiar solo texto. Todos los dem&aacute;s campos se copian autom&aacute;ticamente.</span>
        <span class="en">In Fiori Manage G/L Account Master Data, with account AE0001## on screen &rarr; <strong>Copy</strong> button &rarr; enter the new number and change text only. All other fields are copied automatically.</span>
      </div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-card" data-unit="u3"><div class="ex-header" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="ex-num">EJ 8</span><div><div class="ex-title"><span class="es">Create Profit Centers, Cost Centers, and Segments</span><span class="en">Create Profit Centers, Cost Centers, and Segments</span></div><div class="ex-sub">CC &rarr; PC &rarr; Segment</div></div><span class="chevron">&#8250;</span></div>
    <div class="ex-body">
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body"><span class="es">Fiori Manage Profit Centers &rarr; crear Segment (SEG##) primero.</span><span class="en">Fiori Manage Profit Centers &rarr; create Segment (SEG##) first.</span></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body"><span class="es">Crear Profit Center (PC##): CO Area=A000 | Segment=SEG## | CoCd=GR##.</span><span class="en">Create Profit Center (PC##): CO Area=A000 | Segment=SEG## | CoCd=GR##.</span></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body"><span class="es">Fiori Manage Cost Centers &rarr; Cost Center (COCE##): CO Area=A000 | Profit Center=PC## | CoCd=GR##.</span><span class="en">Fiori Manage Cost Centers &rarr; Cost Center (COCE##): CO Area=A000 | Profit Center=PC## | CoCd=GR##.</span></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-card" data-unit="u3"><div class="ex-header" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="ex-num">EJ 9</span><div><div class="ex-title"><span class="es">Create BP Groupings, Customer Account Groups &amp; CVI</span><span class="en">Create BP Groupings, Customer Account Groups &amp; CVI</span></div><div class="ex-sub">Same Numbers &middot; External Number Range &middot; <span class="es">Ceros iniciales obligatorios</span><span class="en">Leading zeros required</span></div></div><span class="chevron">&#8250;</span></div>
    <div class="ex-body">
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">BP Grouping (number range interno)</span><span class="en">BP Grouping (internal number range)</span>:</strong>
        <span class="step-path">Cross-App Components &rarr; SAP Business Partner &rarr; Basic Settings &rarr; Number Ranges and Groupings &rarr; Define Number Ranges</span>
        <span class="es">Crear number range interno (campo External = sin marcar) &rarr; luego en <em>Define Groupings and Assign Number Ranges</em> crear el grouping AC## y asignarle ese rango.</span>
        <span class="en">Create internal number range (External field = unchecked) &rarr; then in <em>Define Groupings and Assign Number Ranges</em> create grouping AC## and assign the range to it.</span>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Customer Account Group (number range externo)</span><span class="en">Customer Account Group (external number range)</span>:</strong>
        <span class="step-path">FA &rarr; AR/AP &rarr; Customer Accounts &rarr; Master Data &rarr; Define Account Groups with Screen Layout (Customers)</span>
        <span class="es">Copiar el grupo KUNA como base (Copy as...) &rarr; renombrar D## &rarr; configurar field status si es necesario (Required/Optional por secci&oacute;n). Luego en <em>Create Number Ranges for Customer Accounts</em> crear el rango con campo <strong>External = marcado</strong>.</span>
        <span class="en">Copy group KUNA as base (Copy as...) &rarr; rename D## &rarr; configure field status if needed (Required/Optional per section). Then in <em>Create Number Ranges for Customer Accounts</em> create the range with <strong>External = checked</strong>.</span>
        <div class="alert alert-red" style="margin-top:8px">
          <strong>&#9888;&#65039; <span class="es">Ceros iniciales &mdash; regla cr&iacute;tica</span><span class="en">Leading zeros &mdash; critical rule</span>: </strong>
          <span class="es">Al introducir los n&uacute;meros del rango en el campo de Customer Account Number Ranges, <strong>los ceros iniciales son obligatorios</strong> para completar la longitud total del campo. El sistema no los a&ntilde;ade autom&aacute;ticamente. Si el rango conceptual es 200100&ndash;200199, se debe escribir <strong>000200100&ndash;000200199</strong>. Omitirlos produce error o solapamiento con otros rangos.</span>
          <span class="en">When entering range numbers in the Customer Account Number Ranges field, <strong>leading zeros are mandatory</strong> to fill the full field length. The system does not add them automatically. If the conceptual range is 200100&ndash;200199, you must type <strong>000200100&ndash;000200199</strong>. Omitting them causes an error or overlap with other ranges.</span>
        </div>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Vincular BP Grouping con Customer Account Group (CVI)</span><span class="en">Link BP Grouping with Customer Account Group (CVI)</span>:</strong>
        <span class="step-path">Cross-App &rarr; Master Data Synchronization &rarr; CVI &rarr; Settings for Customer Integration &rarr; Define Number Assignment for Direction BP to Customer</span>
        <span class="es">New Entries: Grouping=AC## | Account group=D## | marcar <strong>Same Numbers</strong>. Este flag es el que garantiza que el BP y el cliente reciban el mismo n&uacute;mero al crearse.</span>
        <span class="en">New Entries: Grouping=AC## | Account group=D## | check <strong>Same Numbers</strong>. This flag ensures the BP and customer receive the same number when created.</span>
      </div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-card" data-unit="u3"><div class="ex-header" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="ex-num">EJ 10-11</span><div><div class="ex-title"><span class="es">Edit Customers/Vendors, Field Status (3 fuentes) &amp; Sensitive Fields</span><span class="en">Edit Customers/Vendors, Field Status (3 sources) &amp; Sensitive Fields</span></div><div class="ex-sub"><span class="es">Account Group &middot; Activity &middot; BP Role &middot; Doble control &middot; FK08</span><span class="en">Account Group &middot; Activity &middot; BP Role &middot; Dual control &middot; FK08</span></div></div><span class="chevron">&#8250;</span></div>
    <div class="ex-body">
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">10</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong><span class="es">Por qu&eacute; un campo puede aparecer como no editable</span><span class="en">Why a field may appear as non-editable</span>:</strong>
        <span class="es">Al intentar modificar el Sort Key de un BP/Cliente y el campo aparece en modo <em>Display</em> (no editable), no basta con revisar el Account Group. Hay que verificar las <strong>tres fuentes de Field Status</strong>. En este caso, la causa es que la Activity &ldquo;Change Customer (Centrally)&rdquo; tiene ese campo como <strong>Display</strong>, lo que tiene prioridad sobre el Optional del Account Group.</span>
        <span class="en">When trying to change the Sort Key of a BP/Customer and the field appears in <em>Display</em> mode (non-editable), it is not enough to check the Account Group. You must check all <strong>three Field Status sources</strong>. In this case, the cause is that the Activity &ldquo;Change Customer (Centrally)&rdquo; has that field set to <strong>Display</strong>, which takes priority over the Optional in the Account Group.</span>
        <span class="step-path">FA &rarr; AR/AP &rarr; Customer Accounts &rarr; Master Data &rarr; Define Screen Layout per Activity (Customers) &rarr; Change Customer (Centrally)</span>
        <div class="alert alert-blue" style="margin-top:8px">
          <span class="es"><strong>Regla de prioridad entre las 3 fuentes</strong>: siempre gana el estado m&aacute;s restrictivo. Suppress &gt; Display &gt; Required &gt; Optional. Si la Activity dice Display y el Account Group dice Optional &rarr; el resultado es <strong>Display</strong>.</span>
          <span class="en"><strong>Priority rule between the 3 sources</strong>: the most restrictive status always wins. Suppress &gt; Display &gt; Required &gt; Optional. If Activity says Display and Account Group says Optional &rarr; the result is <strong>Display</strong>.</span>
        </div>
      </div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-num">11</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong>Sensitive Fields:</strong>
        <span class="step-path">FA &rarr; AR/AP &rarr; Supplier Accounts &rarr; Master Data &rarr; Define Sensitive Fields for Dual Control</span>
        <span class="es">Marcar los campos que requieren doble control (ej. Search Term 1, datos bancarios, cuenta de reconciliaci&oacute;n). Cuando alguien modifica un campo sensible, el cambio queda <strong>pendiente de confirmaci&oacute;n</strong> hasta que otro usuario con autorizaci&oacute;n lo aprueba con la transacci&oacute;n <strong>FK08</strong> (para vendors). Solo entonces el cambio es efectivo en el sistema.</span>
        <span class="en">Mark the fields requiring dual control (e.g. Search Term 1, bank data, reconciliation account). When someone changes a sensitive field, the change remains <strong>pending confirmation</strong> until another authorized user approves it with transaction <strong>FK08</strong> (for vendors). Only then does the change take effect in the system.</span>
      </div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

